Sanlam May Cut 70 Jobs in Pension Fund Division, I-Net Says

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-04-16T13:11:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/sanlam-may-cut-70-jobs-in-pension-fund-division-i-net-says.html
Sanlam Ltd. (SLM)  has begun talks with
South African labor union Solidarity about cutting 70 jobs in
its pension fund division, I-Net Bridge reported, citing union
spokeswoman, Ilze Nieuwoudt.  The insurance company told employees in February that they
would be retrenched in May following a reorganization of the
unit, which is based at the head office in Bellville, near  Cape
Town , the  news agency  said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
